President Biden called Prime Minister Kishida of Japan to express his condolences and sadness over the shooting death of former Prime Minister Abe Shinzo. The President emphasized his support for Japan and its people during this time of mourning. He also highlighted the significance of Abe's legacy, including his vision for a free and open Indo-Pacific and the establishment of the QUAD meetings. The two leaders discussed the enduring strength of Japan's democracy and how Abe's legacy will continue to be honored as they work together to defend peace and democracy.